### Claude Code ###
# Local settings can end up recording real secrets inside allowlisted command strings
# (e.g. a command that was run with a real password inline) - never shared/committed.
.claude/

### macOS ###
.DS_Store

### Environment / secrets ###
# Local env files can hold real secrets (DB passwords, API keys) - never committed.
# .env.example is intentionally NOT ignored below, so a template with no real values can
# still be shared via git.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

